Residents of Raitigo in Borabu constituency have raised concerns about fresh incidents of cattle rustling. In the last one month, residents said a total of 30 cows had been stolen with no suspects arrested. The latest incident happened two days ago when 10 cows were stolen. The residents said hardly a day passes without animals being lost to rustling and taken to Bomet. They called on the national government to restart the stalled Raitigo Police Post project.